# shadcn/ui Guidelines

## Component Usage

-   Always use shadcn/ui components when available
-   Customize components through className props and CSS variables
-   Follow shadcn/ui naming conventions
-   Use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes

## State Management

-   Use React's built-in state management (useState, useReducer)
-   Consider Zustand for complex global state
-   Use React Query/TanStack Query for server state
-   Prefer local state over global state when possible

## Best Practices

-   Import shadcn/ui components before custom components
-   Use TypeScript interfaces for all component props
-   Implement proper accessibility attributes
-   Follow consistent naming patterns for component files

## Documentation & References

-   Use Context7 MCP server for shadcn/ui component documentation and examples
-   Query Context7 for Radix UI primitives documentation when customizing components
-   Reference Context7 for Tailwind CSS utility patterns and best practices
-   Leverage Context7's examples for accessible component implementations
